article.headline: Evansville 93, Campbell 71
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Matt Webster scored 19 points as Evansville beat Campbell 83-71 Saturday night. Bradley Strickland had 15 and Kyle Anslinger 14 for the Purple Aces (4-3), who led 42-38 after the first half. Maurice Latham had a double-double with 17 points and 12 rebounds for the Camels (3-4). Eric Smith led Campbell with 20 and Ruell Pringle had 16. The Camels outrebounded the Aces 45-41, but Evansville outscored Campbell 32-22 in the paint. Both teams scored 17 points off turnovers. But Evansville outshot Campbell overall with 48.3 percent (28-of-58) for the game, compared with 30.2 percent (19-of-63) for the Camels. The Purple Aces scored 30 points off the bench. The Camels bench had 14.
